      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">The static bypass switch has its own controller. If the
output voltage goes out of tolerance due to a malfunction in the main
controller, the static bypass switch controller becomes active and
independent. Following a malfunction in the main controller, the static
bypass switch controller takes over and transfers immediately to static
bypass.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">Under normal operating conditions, the static bypass
switch is fully controlled by the UPS controller. The static bypass
switch controller analyses the control signals from the UPS controller,
performs the corresponding tasks, and returns a status signal to the
UPS controller. If the communication fails, the static bypass switch
can operate independently.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">The firmware mainly performs the
following tasks:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Measures the control frequency coming from the UPS controller
and reacts accordingly</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Controls the thyristors</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Generates a status feedback signal for the UPS controller</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Monitors the PSU</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Controls three LEDs and two open collector outputs to display
the actual state</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Measures and evaluates the system output voltage</p>
               </li>
            </ul>
         </p>
      </section>
