      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">ARM State (Normal Operation)</title>
         <p class="- topic/p ">When the control
signal is lost in ARM state, the output voltage is monitored by the
fast-detector during 500 ms:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">If the output voltage remains OK, the static bypass switch
switches to <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">DISARM</uicontrol> after 500 ms.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">If the output voltage is lost within these 500 ms, the static
bypass switch switches to <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">FIRE</uicontrol> state.</p>
               </li>
            </ul>After the static bypass switch has switched to <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">FIRE</uicontrol> state, it again monitors the output voltage (RMS detector and DC
detector):<ul class="- topic/ul ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">If the voltage is lost, the static bypass switch switches to <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">ERROR</uicontrol> state. A reset is then required in order to turn
on the static bypass switch again. Within the first 200 ms after switching
to <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">FIRE</uicontrol>, the static bypass switch does not
switch off.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">If DC is detected on the output, the static bypass switch switches
to <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">ERROR</uicontrol> state. A reset is then required in
order to turn on the static bypass switch again. Within the first
200 ms after switching to <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">FIRE</uicontrol>, the static
bypass switch does not switch off.</p>
               </li>
            </ul>
         </p>
      </section>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">FIRE State (Requested or Temporary Static Bypass Operation)</title>
         <p class="- topic/p ">When the control signal is lost in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">FIRE</uicontrol> state, the static bypass switch stays in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">FIRE</uicontrol> state. The static bypass switch monitors the output voltage (RMS
detector and DC detector):<ul class="- topic/ul ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">If the voltage is lost, the static bypass switch switches to <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">ERROR</uicontrol> state. A reset is then required in order to turn
on the static bypass switch again.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">If DC is detected on the output, the static bypass switch switches
to <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">ERROR</uicontrol> state. A reset is then required in
order to turn on the static bypass switch again.</p>
               </li>
            </ul>
         </p>
      </section>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Regaining Control over the Static Bypass Switch</title>
         <p class="- topic/p ">When the UPS controller recovers from an inoperable state or a
cable is reconnected, control over the static bypass switch can be
regained.<ul class="- topic/ul ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">If the static bypass switch is independently in <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">FIRE</uicontrol> state, control cannot be regained. A firmware restart
(reset) is required.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">If the static bypass switch is in <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">ERROR</uicontrol> state due to independent switching off from <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">FIRE</uicontrol> state (low voltage or DC detection), control cannot be regained.
A firmware restart (reset) is required.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">If the static bypass switch is in another state, it reacts
immediately to the regained control signal.</p>
               </li>
            </ul>
         </p>
      </section>
